Version 1.0

ncurses based program to practice touch type.

compile with g++ -std=c++11 -lncurses type.cpp

The text provided for training is static.

As you press the correct keys the text color gets inverted, if the key is wrong a beep is played.
You don't have to backspace to correct errors, just pressing the key corresponding to the character under the cursor.

At the end you get the average milliseconds between each right key. 
